Questions:
1. What does "spatial capabilities" indicate for a SQL database?
  A spatial database is a database that is specially designed to store, manage, and analyze data related to geographic locations and shapes. 
  In simple terms, it’s a database that understands maps and locations.
  Unlike a regular database that stores text and numbers, a spatial database can store geometries and understand how they relate to each other in space.
  All 3 SQL options in Azure have "spatial capabilities" (i.e. Azure SQL DB, SQL managed instance, SQL on a VM). Difference is in management, compatibility, and control level.
  Azure SQL Database supports SQL Server spatial capabilities and minimizes general administrative overhead. SQL Managed Instance has higher administrative overhead than Azure SQL Database & "SQL on AVM" has highest admin overhead.

2. What is "Azure Synapse analytics" pipeline? 
  Azure Synapse Analytics allows you to transform data, links data to Power BI, and performs near real-time log analysis. 

